- DAX Formula
- Analytical Use Case

---

## ðŸ”¹ Loan Amount by Purpose

### **Measure**
```DAX
Loan Amount by Purpose =
SUMX(
    FILTER('Loan_default', NOT(ISBLANK('Loan_default'[LoanAmount]))),
    'Loan_default'[LoanAmount]
)
Description
Calculates the total loan amount by iterating over non-blank loan values.

Usage
Used in Line Chart

Analyzes loan trends across different loan purposes

Alternative approach also implemented using filters and visuals (without DAX)

ðŸ”¹ Average Income by Employment Type
Measure
DAX
Copy code
Average Income by Employement Type =
CALCULATE(
    AVERAGE('Loan_default'[Income]),
    ALLEXCEPT('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[EmploymentType])
)
Description
Computes average income while keeping Employment Type as the only active filter.

Key Concept
ALLEXCEPT() removes all filters except Employment Type

ðŸ”¹ Default Rate by Employment Type
Measure
DAX
Copy code
Default Rate by Employment Type =
VAR totalRecords = COUNTROWS(ALL('Loan_default'))
VAR defaultCases =
    COUNTROWS(FILTER('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[Default] = TRUE()))
RETURN
CALCULATE(
    DIVIDE(defaultCases, totalRecords),
    ALLEXCEPT('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[EmploymentType])
)
Description
Calculates the default rate segmented by employment type.

Insight
Identifies employment categories with higher credit risk

ðŸ”¹ Average Loan Amount by Age Group
Measure
DAX
Copy code
Average Loan Amount by Age Group =
AVERAGEX(
    VALUES('Loan_default'[Age Group]),
    AVERAGE('Loan_default'[LoanAmount])
)
Description
Calculates average loan amount for each age group.

Key Concept
VALUES() creates a virtual table of distinct age groups

ðŸ”¹ Default Rate by Year
Measure
DAX
Copy code
Default Rate by Year =
VAR totalLoan =
    CALCULATE(
        COUNTROWS('Loan_default'),
        ALLEXCEPT('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[Year])
    )
VAR default =
    CALCULATE(
        COUNTROWS(FILTER('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[Default] = TRUE())),
        ALLEXCEPT('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[Year])
    )
RETURN
DIVIDE(default, totalLoan) * 100
Description
Computes yearly default rate percentage.

Usage
Trend analysis of loan defaults over time

ðŸ”¹ Average Loan Amount (High Credit Score)
Measure
DAX
Copy code
Average Loan Amt (High Credit) =
AVERAGEX(
    FILTER('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[Credit Score Bins] = "High"),
    'Loan_default'[LoanAmount]
)
Description
Calculates average loan amount for borrowers with high credit scores.

ðŸ”¹ Median Loan Amount by Credit Score Bins
Measure
DAX
Copy code
Median by Credit Score bins =
MEDIANX('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[LoanAmount])
Description
Returns the median loan amount, reducing the impact of outliers.

ðŸ”¹ Total Loan Amount (Credit Bins â€“ Adults)
Measure
DAX
Copy code
Total Loan (Credit Bins) =
CALCULATE(
    SUM('Loan_default'[LoanAmount]),
    'Loan_default'[Age Group] = "Adults",
    ALLEXCEPT(
        'Loan_default',
        'Loan_default'[Age],
        'Loan_default'[Age Group],
        'Loan_default'[CreditScore],
        'Loan_default'[Credit Score Bins]
    )
)
Description
Calculates total loan amount for adult borrowers, segmented by credit score bins.

ðŸ”¹ Total Loan Amount (Middle Age Adults)
Measure
DAX
Copy code
Total Loan (Middle Age Adults) =
SUMX(
    FILTER('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[Age Group] = "Middle Age Adults"),
    'Loan_default'[LoanAmount]
)
Description
Computes total loan disbursement for middle-aged adults.

ðŸ”¹ Loan Count by Education Type
Measure
DAX
Copy code
Loan by Education Type =
COUNTROWS(
    FILTER('Loan_default', NOT(ISBLANK('Loan_default'[LoanID])))
)
Description
Counts total loans issued across different education levels.

ðŸ”¹ Year-over-Year (YoY) Loan Amount Change
Measure
DAX
Copy code
YOY Loan Amount Change =
DIVIDE(
    CALCULATE(
        SUM('Loan_default'[LoanAmount]),
        'Loan_default'[Year] =
            YEAR(MAX('Loan_default'[Loan_Date_DD_MM_YYYY]))
    )
    -
    CALCULATE(
        SUM('Loan_default'[LoanAmount]),
        'Loan_default'[Year] =
            YEAR(MAX('Loan_default'[Loan_Date_DD_MM_YYYY])) - 1
    ),
    CALCULATE(
        SUM('Loan_default'[LoanAmount]),
        'Loan_default'[Year] =
            YEAR(MAX('Loan_default'[Loan_Date_DD_MM_YYYY])) - 1
    ),
    0
) * 100
Description
Measures annual growth or decline in loan amount.

ðŸ”¹ Year-over-Year (YoY) Default Loan Change
Measure
DAX
Copy code
YOY Default Loan Change =
DIVIDE(
    CALCULATE(
        COUNTROWS(FILTER('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[Default] = "True")),
        'Loan_default'[Year] =
            YEAR(MAX('Loan_default'[Loan_Date_DD_MM_YYYY]))
    )
    -
    CALCULATE(
        COUNTROWS(FILTER('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[Default] = "True")),
        'Loan_default'[Year] =
            YEAR(MAX('Loan_default'[Loan_Date_DD_MM_YYYY])) - 1
    ),
    CALCULATE(
        COUNTROWS(FILTER('Loan_default', 'Loan_default'[Default] = "True")),
        'Loan_default'[Year] =
            YEAR(MAX('Loan_default'[Loan_Date_DD_MM_YYYY])) - 1
    ),
    0
) * 100
Description
Tracks YoY change in loan defaults.

ðŸ”¹ Year-to-Date (YTD) Loan Amount
Measure
DAX
Copy code
YTD Loan Amount =
CALCULATE(
    SUM('Loan_default'[LoanAmount]),
    DATESYTD('Loan_default'[Loan_Date_DD_MM_YYYY].[Date]),
    ALLEXCEPT(
        'Loan_default',
        'Loan_default'[Credit Score Bins],
        'Loan_default'[MaritalStatus]
    )
)
Description
Calculates cumulative loan amount from the beginning of the year to date.

ðŸ“Š Conclusion
These DAX measures collectively enable:

Risk analysis

Trend identification

Borrower segmentation

Time-based performance tracking

They form the analytical backbone of the Loan Default Power BI Dashboard.

